In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer provides updates on various topics. He mentions that President Trump signed an executive order on offshore energy development, which aims to move towards energy security while maintaining environmental stewardship. Spicer also notes that the President will be speaking at the National Rifle Association's Leadership Forum and will highlight his accomplishments during his first 100 days in office. He briefly mentions progress on healthcare efforts and the spending plan, as well as discussions on the THAAD missile system and the Paris agreement. Spicer confirms that Senator Ted Cruz is on the plane and will also address the NRA. He mentions that the President will talk about his commitment to the Second Amendment and his views on firearms policy in his speech. The briefing concludes with Spicer mentioning the possibility of the President visiting Israel and other travel updates.